cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SE

This paper involves the integration of geophysical and flow data to characterize subsurface systems, which is a common problem in computational engineering (cs.CE). The paper also presents a non-intrusive sequential inversion framework, which involves statistical and physics-based approaches, indicating the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS) techniques. The paper also involves the estimation of subsurface parameters, which is a common problem in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper involves the demonstration of the efficacy of the proposed approach through a synthetic example, indicating the use of software engineering (cs.SE) techniques.
